column2: Sunny and north wind.  Lots of copepods in three foot water sample.
sky clear- moderate wind- rain 4 inches over weekend- some green colonies and "grass clippings" algae- was murky as compared to usual at this time of year- was much clearer last week
partly cloudy- slight wind- 16.1 deg C air temp- "grass clippings" algal filaments in water- slight algal bloom
partly cloudy- nice day- water clear
clear sky- slight NW wind- water clear- beautiful
sunny- clear- water color brownish green
Greg Holmes and park staff performed monitoring. Clear- sunny- breezy- 70.
Liz Oleson + Kelsey Rule performed monitoring.  Clear- sunny- humid- slight breeze- 85- 1.5 inches rain 7 days prior.
Liz Oleson- Kelsey Rule- Donna Sefton performed monitoring. Clear- sunny- humid- slight breeze. 85. 1.5 inches rain 7 days prior.
Kelsey Rule- B. Yanna- C. Wepking performed monitoring.  Cloudy- 72- windy-  sunny.  Too windy to hold boat for entire DO/temperature profile.
Kelsey Rule- B. Yanna- C. Wepking performed monitoring.  Partly cloudy- 72- slight breeze.
Kelsey Rule- Liz Oleson- B. Yanna- Paul Kosharek performed monitoring.  Hot- sunny- 80- slight wind.
Kelsey Rule- Liz Oleson- B. Yanna- Paul performed monitoring.  Hot- sunny- 80- slight wind.
Dan Welsh- Liz Oleson- Donna Sefton performed monitoring.  Hot- partly cloudy- 80- slight breeze from NE.
Dan Welsh- Liz Oleson- Paul Kosharek. M. Pienel- Donna Sefton performed monitoring.  Hot- partly cloudy- 80- slight breeze from NE.
Dave Marshall and Richard Wedepohl performed monitoring.  Sunny- hot- 92.
Dave Marshall- Richard Wedepohl performed monitoring.  Sunny- hot- 92.

Kelsey M- Brittnee- Taylor- Heather- Megan performed monitoring. Partly cloudy- 88- breezy- 8 inches of rain 8/4 Kelsey M- Brittnee- Taylor- Heather- Megan performed monitoring. Partly cloudy- 88- breezy- 8 inches of rain 8/4

Kelsey M- Brittnee- Taylor- Heather- and Megan performed monitoring.  Sunny- cloudy- 88- 8 inches rain on 8/4. Kelsey M- Brittnee- Taylor- Heather- and Megan performed monitoring.  Sunny- cloudy- 88- 8 inches rain on 8/4.

Greg Holmes- park staff and Donna Sefton performed monitoring.  Sunny- 80- 21 inches of rain since 8/4- blue-green algae bloom- Aphanizomen "grass clippings" and small round colonies evident.  Beach much greener than rest of lake.

Greg Holmes- park staff- and Donna Sefton performed monitoring.  Sunny- 80- 21 inches of rain since 8/4- blue-green algae bloom- Aphanizomen "grass clippings" and small round colonies visible.  Beach much greener than rest of lake.
Overcast- 60- slight breeze- some EWM near dock- mostly sago pondweed around lake out to 30'.  Algae bloom. 14" rain in last 3 weeks.

Overcast- 60- small waves- algae bloom- 14" rain in last 3 weeks; some EWM near rental dock- otherwise a variety of plants (coontail- elodea- flatstem- sago pondweed- etc).  Mostly sago pondweed around out to about 30'.

Mostly cloudy-wind 5 mph- 70s.  Much less aquatic vegetation than usual- probably because of turbidity earlier in the year due to all the rain.  Mostly sago pondweed + coontail to 20-30' out on shoreline.  Only EWM observed was patch off point to right of Pontoon Bay in about 10' of water and 20 - 30' out.
Clear- 76- slight breeze out of N.
Partly cloudy- slight breeze- 70.  No EWM visible.
Partly cloudy- calm- 88- humid- 5" rain on 6/18- 2 patches of EWM where originally found (Pontoon Bay + first bush between left + right dam).
Partly cloudy- calm- 88- humid-5" rain on 6/18. 2patches of EWM where originallyfound (Pontoon Bay + between dams - first bush right of left dam)
Partly cloudy- 78- wind from NE at 10 mph- green algae bloom.  No visual evidence of EWM.
Partly cloudy- 78- wind from NE at 10 mph; Green algae bloom (no observation of obvious Aphanizomenon or Microcystis..

Cloudy- calm- 68- humid- rain 1.4" 7/21/12.  Small patches of EWM found Pontoon Bay + on E shore out from small bent willow + pine. Blobs of dark- decaying filamentous algae.  Curly-leaf pondweed mostly died off- getting blue-green algae bloom - tiny round green algae + Aphanizomenon flakes visible.

Cloudy- calm- 68- humid- rain 1.4" on 7/21. Patches of EWM in Pontoon Bay + on E shore out from small bent willow.  Blobs of dark decaying filamentous algae. Curly-leaf pondweed mostly died off- getting blue-green algae bloom- as evidenced by tiny round green algae (Microcystis ) + Aphanizomenon flakes.

Calm. Small green algae in water- not many visible plants except coontail- no EWM seen between dams.  In Pontoon Bay- Ranunculus died back- more Heteranthera- very little EWM seen- but visibility on 4'.

Clear- 75- sllght breeze- small green algae in water. Not many plants visible except coontail.  No EWM seen between dams.  In Pontoon Bay- Ranunculus died back- more Heteranthera- very little EWM observed- but visibility only 4'.

Partly cloudy- 57- wind WSW 5 mph.  Boat survey: no EWM observed between dams or in pontoon bay or shoreline.  Lots of curly-leaf pondweed. Ranunculus blankets bottom in shallow areas of Pontoon Bay- coontail in other areas 4-11'.  No Heteranthera observed.

party cloudy- 57; wind WSW 5 mph; boat survey- no Eurasian water milfoil- curly-leaf pondweed- abundant; water buttercup + coontail common in other areas. party cloudy- 57; wind WSW 5 mph; boat survey- no Eurasian water milfoil- curly-leaf pondweed- abundant; water buttercup + coontail common in other areas. partly cloudy- 57- wind WSW 5 mph; boat survey found no Eurasian watermilfoil.  Curly leaf pondweed abundant; water buttercup and coontail common in shallows. partly cloudy- 57- wind WSW 5 mph; boat survey found no Eurasian watermilfoil.  Curly leaf pondweed abundant; water buttercup and coontail common in shallows. Water stargrass not visible.
clear- calm to slight breeze- 75- Eurasian watermilfoil abundant on sand ridge between dams; patches in Pontoon Bay.
with Laura Sefton. Clear- 75- slight breezem EWM abundant on sand ridge between dams.
clear- calm- 70s. Eurasian watermilfoil abundant on sand ridge between dams- some patches in Pontoon Bay.

cloudy- slight breeze- ripple waves; treated for Eurasian watermilfoil on sand ridge between dams. cloudy- slight breeze- ripple waves; slight drizzle; treated for Eurasian watermilfoil on sand ridge between dams. cloudy- slight breeze- ripple waves; slight drizzle; treated for Eurasian watermilfoil on 6/10/10 in sand ridge between dams.EWM already showing signs of dying - turning medium brown. cloudy- slight breeze- ripple waves; slight drizzle; Bradd Sims treated for Eurasian watermilfoil in sand ridge between dams.
Partly cloudy- 80- slight breeze- not much rain in past week- tiny green algae visible.

partly cloudy- slight breeze- 80s- not much rain for awhile; small green algae colonies in water; boat survey found no Eurasian watermilfoil. partly cloudy- calm to slight breeze- 80s; small green algae colonies in water; boat survey found no Eurasian water milfoi.
No visual evidence of Eurasian watermilfoil.
Cloudy- 70s- rain 8/13 washed out a lot of scum + plants - lot less plants than on 8/12.  No visual evidence of EWM
cloudy- 70s- rain 8/13 washed out scum + some plants.  Lot less plants than 8/12. No visual evidence of Eurasian watermilfoil.
no visual evidence of Eurasian watermilfoil.
Partly cloudy- breeze- 80- Curly-leaf + sago pondweed- + coontail primary plants.  No EWM observed.
partly cloudy- breeze- 80 degrees- curly leaf pondweed- sago pondweed- coontaiil- but no Eurasian Watermilfoil visible.

Doing aquatic plant survey with John Skogorboe- sunny- calm to slight breeze- 70's.  Only very small patch of Eurasian water milfoil found on edge of S bay-. Curly leaf pondweed. abundant.- with coontail- water stargrass + water buttercup common in shallower areas.
Cloudy- slight breeze- 70s.  Surface water temp 71.6. Curly-leaf pondweed mostly gone- some narrow leaved pondweed (sago ) + coontail. No EWM.-
cloudy- slight breeze- 70's; no EWM seen; curly-leaf pondweed mostly gone- lot of narrow-leaved (sago ) pondweed and coontail. Water stargrass + water buttercup in shallower areas-
slight breeze- 80's; lake green w/mcroscopic algae (not blue greens Aphanizomen or Microcystis obvious).
Sunny- calm- 77.  Can see Aphanomenon flakes in water.  Also tiny green balls- probably Microcystis.
clear- calm- 78; no EWM found- but water murky + hard to see.
partly cloudy- 70's- slight breeze- no EWM visible- lot of coontail.;dredging Pontoon Bay
Water temp 53- air temp 50; wind SE 10 MPH; tiny green algae in water; Curly-leaf pondweed abundant on sand ridge- a little coontail.  Left dam Secchi = 9'.

Clear- 80s- slight breeze from SW.  Sand ridge - no EWM- abundant curly-leaf pondweed- with some sago pondweed and coontail on sand ridge. Pontoon Bay - curly-leaf pondweed- water buttercup- coontail.   Left dam Secchi = 10'.

70s- NW wind 5-10 MPH- mostly cloudy- algae bloom with little green particles.  Sand ridge - no EWM with rake tosses or visually; curly-leaf pondweed mostly senesced- abundant coontail- sago pondweed + water buttercup.  Pontoon Bay - no EWM- has some curly-leaf pondweed- along with coontail- elodea- water buttercup- Chara- water stargrass. Fishermen say lake turned over on 6/2/12.  Was in 50s + 60s and very windy in previous few days. Left dam Secchi = 6'.

Sunny- 80s- slight breeze- small green algae- no obvious blue-greens- no rain for a long time. Left dam Secchi = 7.5'.  Sand ridge - no EWM- curly-leaf pondweed mostly senesced- sago pondweed senescing- coontail abundant.  Pontoon Bay - no EWM-  Many other natives (coontail- sago pondweed- water buttercup- elodea- Chara- water stargrass- small leaved pondweed).  Sago + water buttercup senescing.

partly cloudy- 80s- blue-green algae bloom - "paint slick" near concessions + beach.  Hot- dry weather.  Sand ridge - no EWM- mostly sago pondweed (senescing) and coontail.  Pontoon Bay - no EWM.  Right dam Secchi = 4'.

81; partly cloudy- wind NNW 3-5 mph; hydrogen sulfide smell by dam; tiny green algae in water.  Main aquatic plants are sago pondweed and coontail- which are senescing.  No EWM observed. Right dam Secchi = 3.75.
cloudy- calm- 80's; tiny green algae particles in water; no obvious blue greens; major plants on sand ridge are senescing sago pondweed and coontail.  No EWM observed.  Left dam Secchi = 3'.
No aquatic plants found in bays- where there is usually still a lot of coontail and other plants at this time of year.
clear; calm; brown floating decayed algae clumps and aquatic plant fragments; larger zooplankton (Daphnia) visible- along with small white particles in water
Partly cloudy- slight breeze- floating filamentous algae; curly-leaf pondweed- coontail visible- no Eurasian Watermilfoil.
70s- clear- slight breeze; pollen on water and milky appearance in shallows. Curly-leaf and sago pondweed and coontail visible.  No Eurasian watermilfoil.
70s- clear- slight breeze; Lots of curly-leaf and sago pondweed and coontail.  No Eurasian watermilfoil observed.
Clear- slight breeze- 80s; no Eurasian watermilfoil; curly-leaf and sago pondweed clumps floating + senescing after being uprooted by motors
Partly sunny- 80s- humid; 10-12" rain in last 5 days (was up 4 ft and landing was flooded on 6/23 + 6/24)  No Eurasian watermilfoil observed.

75- partly cloudy- calm.  Small green particles in water.  Sand ridge: coontail- sago pondweed- water stargrass + filamentous algae- no Eurasian watermilfoil observed.  Pontoon Bay: coontail- sago pondweed- water stargrass- Elodea + filamentous algae- no Eurasian watermilfoil observed.

70s- clear- slight breeze; Very green- but Aphanizamenon- Microcystis- and Anabaena colonies visible. Actively growing aquatic plants mostly gone- some senescing coontail- sago pondweed- water stargrass- filamentous algae + duckweed.  No Eurasian watermilfoil observed.
85- partly cloudy- slight breeze.  Not many aquatic plants left.  Just a little coontail and sago pondweed.
80s- partly cloudy- slight breeze.  Very green - like pea soup.

Partly cloudy- calm. Concession dock area: water clear with some filamentous algae + curly-leaf pondweed- lots of panfish.  Boat launch area murky (brown) with no plants near shore. Pontoon bay: some floating filamentous algae- water buttercup just coming up.   Boat/rake survey found no Eurasian watermilfoil.

Partly cloudy- wind from W @ 8 mph. 70's.  Curly leaf pondweed primary plant- but not as much growth as there usually is this time of year. Water stargrass just coming up and some filamentous algae in shoreline areas. Boat/rake survey found no Eurasian water milfoil.

Clear- slight breeze- mostly curly-leaf pondweed.  Sago pondweed- water stargrass- water buttercup just emerging. Not much coontail on bottom on sand ridge.  Boat/rake survey found no Eurasian water milfoil.

Partly cloudy- breeze from SW @ 7 mph- 80's.  Lots of curly-leaf pondweed- some sago pondweed- little coontail.  Water stargrass and water buttercup coming up.  Boat/rake survey found no Eurasian water milfoil.
Clear- calm. Lots of curly-leaf pondweed and narrow leaf pondweed. Some elodea- coontail- and sago pondweed in shallow areas.  Boat/rake survey found no Eurasian water milfoil.

Partly cloudy- slight breeze.    Boat/rake survey found no Eurasian water milfoil.  Shallows by boat landing has coontail- sago pondweed- elodea- water stargrass- curly-leaf pondweed- water buttercup- narrow leaved pondweed- filamentous algae + duckweed.
Partly cloudy.  Breezy.  Point-intercept aquatic plant survey completed on northern part of lake. No Eurasian water milfoil found.

Partly cloudy- slight breeze- 80's.  Little curly-leaf pondweed.  Mostly sago pondweed on sand ridge. No Eurasian water milfoil observed with boat/rake survey.  Water only slightly green at sample site- most of the rest of the lake- and beach.  Bue-green algae "paint slick" bloom at boat landing.

Partly cloudy- 80's- slight breeze.  Sago pondweed dying off- water stargrass becoming more abundant near shore + by docks.  Potamogen natans between beach and concession dock.  Looks like pea soup near shore. Obvious blue-green algae bloom (probably Microcystis) throughout lake. Recommended post water quality advisory signs.

Partly cloudy- 80's- humid.  Obvious blue-green algae bloom at boat launch- boat concession and beach. Recommended post water quality advisory signs. Aquatic plants decaying. Boat/rake survey found no Eurasian water milfoil.
Partly cloudy- calm- water green- but not an obvious blue-green algae bloom.
Calm- 65. Water green.  Blue-green algae "paint slick" at landing and boat concession area.  Boat/rake survey found no Eurasian water milfoil.  Recommended post water quality advisory signs.

Overcast- slight breeze- Some particles in water and milky color in major inlets. No Eurasian watermilfoil (EWM).  Lush native plant growth (e.g. water buttercup- elodea- small pondweed- coontail) covering bottom in shallow areas.  Curly-leaf pondweed interspersed with other plants in shallow water and emerging near the surface in deeper water.

No Eurasian watermilfoil. Curly-leaf pondweed in deeper water. Lush native plant growth covering bottom in shallower water (e.g.- water buttercup- water stargrass- small pondweed- elodea- sago pondweed).

Clear- slight breeze- ~80.  No EWM.  Mostly curly-leaf pondweed + sago in deeper areas. Lush growth of native plants such as water buttercup. water stargrass- small leaved pondweed- coontail and elodea in shallows.

Clear- slight breeze- ~80.  Aquatic Plant Survey with Jeanne Shearer and Katrina Punze found no EWM- native vegetation in shallows. Beach and boat concession areas being chemically treated with 2-4- D.
Partly cloudy- slight breeze. Aquatic plant survey with Jeanne Scherer and Katrina Punzel found no EWM- with native plant growth in shallows.  Tiny green algae in water.

No EWM. Sago/small leaved pondweed on sand ridge beginning to senesce- not mats like usually are.  Chara and other lush plant growth just S. of beach. Some very small green algae in water- but not aesthetic problem.

Slight breeze- 87- humid.  No EWM. Sago pondweed + other plants in deeper water senescing. Still abundant variety of plants such as water stargrass- Chara- Elodea- coontail- flatstem pondweed in nearshore areas (~2 - 6")-

Calm to slight breeze- ~80.  No EWM.  A little blue green algae.  Lot of water stargrass in shallows (2' - 4"). Most of other plants dying off.  Some build-up of decaying filamentous algae + scum in shallows.
No EWM.  Aquatic plants senescing.  Blue green algae blooming developing.

50s- overcast- small-moderate waves; Strong SW winds + storms previous week stirred up. Plants around piers were water buttercup- Elodea- coontail- curly leaf pondweed; little else in deeper water except CLP- no EWM; small green algae visible; Secchi off handicapped pier 11'.
70s- calm- curly-leaf pondweed in deeper areas- no EWM- water buttercup- P. foliosus- Chara in shallows.

70s- mostly clear- calm to slight breeze; abundant curly-leaf pondweed into deeper water- no EWM; water buttercup- Elodea- Chara- sago pondweed in shallows - more plant growth than usual.  Lot of CLP in beach area.

Lots of plants still around concession dock- beach + fishing pier following treatment.  Curly-leaf pondweed dying- Ranunculus stressed- rest of aquatic plants still ok (water stargrass- elodea- P. foliosus- which is abundant in shallows).
Clear- slight breeze- 85- no EWM- Potamogeton pectinatus abundant in deeper water on sand ridge along with filamentous algae.  Chemical treatment worked around concession- fishing pier- and beach.

Party cloudy- 80- slight breeze- no EWM- small green algae in water.  Treatment areas around concession dock- outer edge of fishing pier- beach worked well. Some P. foliosus- water stargrass + sago pondweed in shallower areas at concession dock.  P. foliosus abundant in shallower areas of fishing pier. Chara- water stargrass- and P. foliosus abundant in non-treated near shore areas. Mostly Potamogeton puscillus on sand ridge.

Lots of decaying duckweed near shore- smelly.  South 1/3 of beach has vegetation + duckweed.  Lots of small (green) algae in water- no really obvious blue-green colonies (Aphanizomenon- Microcystis- Anabaena).

70's- partly sunny- breezy.  Water green with small green algae visible- but no obvious blue-green colonies (Aphanizomenon- Microcystic- Anabaena). Most of aquatic plants senesced. South 1/3 of beach still some plants + muck.  Duckweed near shore.
70s. slight breeze- 4+ in. rain in last few days. Water brown from sediment- few aquatic plants or algae.

70's- slight breeze- mostly sunny. Rain- wind- cool the previous week and much of April. No EWM- Curly-leaf pondweed moderate to abundant- some White water crowfoot- Leafy pondweed- very small green algae in water.

70's- calm- partly cloudy. Rain- wind- cool weather all month. No EWM. Abundant Curly-leaf pondweed in all areas less than 10 ft- impairing swimming and navigation at concession dock and fishing pier. Some White water crowfoot- Coontail- Leafy pondweed and Elodea in shallows by concession dock.

70's- calm- sunny. No EWM. Abundant aquatic plants impairing use around concession dock and fishing pier and S 1/3 of beach. Mostly stringy Slender and Sago pondweeds and Curly-leaf pondweed deeper- White water crowfoot- Coontail- Elodea- and filamentous algae shallower.

70's- slight breeze- clear. No EWM- mostly Sago pondweed on sand ridge 5-10 ft- Chemical treatments right around beach- fishing pier and boat concession worked- White water crowfoot- Curly-leaf pondweed- Coontail- Leafy pondweed and Sago pondweed dying in these areas. Water stargrass is becoming abundant- impairing navigation at concession dock.
70's- slight breeze. No EWM. Very small green algae in water- no evidence of blue-green algae.

SW wind about 12 mph- moderate waves- partly cloudy. Lot of rain in past 2 weeks. Water color brownish-green with some tiny green algae. No EWM. Most plants have died off- except for abundant Water stargrass in shallow areas and some Sago pondweed in deeper areas.

70's- calm- slight breeze- mostly sunny. Water brownish green- tiny green algae- no evidence of blue-green algae. No EWM- mostly Sago pondweed in deeper water- Water stargrass and Coontail near shore. Most other plants have died off. Water stargrass is abundant in shallow areas around concession dock and fishing pier and in S part of beach.
70's- partly cloudy- blight breeze. Water brownish green. No EWM- mostly Sago pondweed in deeper water (dying)- abundant Water stargrass and some Coontail and Curly-leaf pondweed in shallows.

70's- partly cloudy- slight breeze. Water color greenish brown. Mostly Sago pondweed and filamentous algae in deeper water. Abundant Water stargrass- and some Coontail and Curly-leaf pondweed in shallows.

70's- slight breeze- mostly sunny. Water color greenish brown. Abundant Water stargrass in shallows- with Coontail- Chara on NE side of sandbar (across the lake from the beach).  Duckweed- filamentous algae- Chinese mystery snails near shore.
water temp 59- air temp 66- cloudy- breeze 5 mph. Some small curly-leaf pondweed- no other plants visible. No Eurasian watermilfoil.

65- cloudy- calm to 5 mph breeze. 5" rain previous 2 weeks.  No Eurasian watermilfoil. Curly-leaf pondweed abundant on sand ridge- with P. puscillus and sago pondweed in Pontoon Bay- Curly-leaf and P. puscillus abundant at concession dock + fishing pier- along with some filamentous algae- water buttercup- water stargrass- coontail- and elodea- impairing navigation and fishing.

70- cloudy- breezy 5-10 mph- 1.5" rain 6/2-6/3. Curly-leaf pondweed- P. puscillus impairing navigation- fishing + swimming at concession dock- fishing pier- and beach.  Chara- fllamentous algae- water stargrass- coontail also present. Curly-leaf + P. puscillus on sand ridge. Curly-lead with P. puscillus- sago- water buttercup in Pontoon Bay.
70s- clear- calm to slight breeze. No Eurasian watermilfoil. P. puscillus abundant around concession dock- fishing pier- sand ridge- beach. Some curly-leaf pondweed.

70s- wind 10-15 mph- moderate waves- 4" rain week before. Diquat + copper sulfate applied to concession dock- fishing pier- beach on 6/21. Curly-leaf + P. puscillus sensescing around concession dock- not much effect of treatment from fishing pier to beach.

80s- clear- calm to slight breeze. Curly-leaf pondweed- P. puscillus gone around concession dock + fishing pier- senescing elsewhere in lake- decaying filamentous algae + vegetation near shore. Water stargrass in S. 1/3 of beach. Pontoon Bay senescing P. puscillus covered by filamentous algae.

80- humid- breeze 5 mph. algae bloom forming. Concession dock + fishing pier: little vegetation in area treated- some filamentous algae- coontail.  Beach: S. 1/3 water stargrass + coontail. Most plants in lake senesced- nothing visible on sand ridge. Boat launch: water stargrass- some coontail- elodea- filamentous algae- arrowhead- bulrush- cattail.
80s- clear- slight breeze- previous week hot- calm- no rain. Little vegetation. Blue-green algae bloom. Blackhawk L Recreation Area posted Water Quality Advisory signs.
75- calm to 5 mph breeze- humid- 2.5" rain in past 2 days. Still blue-green algae bloom- but not as abundant. Concession dock + S 1/3 of beach: water stargrass impairs navigation.
70s- sunny- slight breeze- ripple waves. 10" rain between 8/20 - 8/30. Blue-green algae bloom like pea soup. Blackhawk L Recreation Area posted Water Quality Advisory signs.
Mostly sunny- slight breeze 0-5 mph. Still algae visible in water- but not as much as on 9/10/18. Most plants have senesced. Some residual blue-green algae pigment on beach.
partly sunny- wind 6-10 mph from NW- small waves- over 3 inches of rain in past 2 days- little plant growth.

80- partly cloudy- calm- 1-1/2" rain 6/24/19; staff says concession dock- handicapped pier- fishing pier- and beach treated 6/25/19; few plants deeper- loose decaying slender + curly-leaf pondweed floating in to shore and in shallows. No EWM.  Hot- calm- weather predicted - with rain- treatment- + nutrients washed in- be watchful for blue-green algae.
80s- partly cloudy- wind 7-10 mph- about 2" rain following hot- humid weather (90s); small green algae in water near concession dock; few aquatic plants.
75- mostly cloudy- calm to slight breeze; abundant water stargrass + elodea at concession dock; slender pondweed deeper; no EWM; some small green algae- no evidence of blue-green algae.
70s- partly cloudy- slight breeze; lot of water stargrass + elodea by concession dock- some slender + curly-leaf pondweed- no EWM.
80- partly cloudy- calm to slight breeze; abundant water stargrass + elodea at concession dock; also coontail- slender + sago pondweed- Chara- + water stargrass at fishing pier.

Calm- mostly sunny- tiny green algae in water- no evidence of blue-greens. No EWM. Concession dock - few plants- mostly Chara + Elodea- Coontail + stargrass just greening up- P. puscillus at end of dock- filamentous algae- duckweed near shore.  Sand Ridge: Curly-leaf pondweed + P. puscillus deeper- Chara- P foliosus- stargrass shallower.  Pontoon Bay: white water crowfoot- P. puscillus- sago. Fishing pier: abundant  P. puscillus- P. foliosus- sago- filamentous algae.

Calm to slight breeze- 80-  Tiny green algae in water- no evidence of  blue-greens. No EWM- Docks: few plants - a little Chara- Elodea- coontail- stargrass. Pontoon Bay: decaying P. puscillus- sago- some Chara + white water crowfoot near shore-
85- sunny- slight waves - wind 5-10 mph from SE. Tiny green algae in water- no evidence of blue-greens.  No EWM. Water stargrass near docks- not much other vegetation.
